27
00:01:40,970 --> 00:01:42,650
[Director Saratswadee Wongsomphet]

28
00:01:45,930 --> 00:01:48,866
If you want to live with me,

29
00:01:48,866 --> 00:01:51,366
then let's move out from here.

30
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,683
Move out from here?

31
00:01:56,683 --> 00:01:59,525
Where can we go?

32
00:01:59,525 --> 00:02:03,000
Just stay here. I don't want you to get into trouble again.

33
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,400
You don't want me to get into trouble,

34
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:08,985
or you don't want to get yourself into trouble?

35
00:02:50,740 --> 00:02:55,112
You... I hope you won't scream like the heroine in a TV series.

36
00:02:55,112 --> 00:02:57,972
I'm not an ignorant heroine.

37
00:02:57,972 --> 00:03:03,200
Then, I hope you won't ask me what I did to you.

38
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:05,760
I'm not that ignorant, either.

39
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:10,520
Which means you're okay with seeing me when you wake up.

40
00:03:12,220 --> 00:03:14,500
I'm okay with it.

41
00:03:16,420 --> 00:03:21,125
But you will not be okay.

42
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:23,920
Are we close?

43
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,380
Why did you come to my home?

44
00:03:26,380 --> 00:03:29,720
Wait. Look around.

45
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,600
Whose home is this?

46
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:34,954
Whose home is this? This is my...

47
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,660
This is my home.

48
00:03:45,890 --> 00:03:47,820
Why am I here?

49
00:03:47,820 --> 00:03:50,020
Because you were drunk.

50
00:03:52,100 --> 00:03:55,180
I was drunk. You brought me to your home because I was drunk?

51
00:03:55,180 --> 00:03:58,020
You really are... Bastard!

52
00:03:58,020 --> 00:03:59,620
Ah! My head.

53
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:03,440
Stop! My head.

54
00:04:05,040 --> 00:04:07,340
What do you want to do?

55
00:04:07,340 --> 00:04:09,760
Stop. It hurts.

56
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:13,186
Don't ask me. Because I have to ask myself

57
00:04:13,186 --> 00:04:16,480
how close I am to you to bring you home.

58
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:19,140
What kind of woman are you? You're dirty and love to lie.

59
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:21,380
- And you were drunk like...
- Don't say that I was drunk like a dog.

60
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:24,886
I didn't say that. You said it yourself.

61
00:04:24,886 --> 00:04:29,120
Listen. I helped you. You should thank me.

62
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:32,100
- I─
- Listen. If I hadn't helped you,

63
00:04:32,100 --> 00:04:34,540
I don't know what you'd be like now.

64
00:04:34,540 --> 00:04:38,300
I put you in a shopping cart. But you were asleep and didn't know what was going on.

65
00:04:38,300 --> 00:04:39,860
What kind of woman are you?

66
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:41,820
- That is to say─
- Listen!

67
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:46,060
Besides being disobedient, you're not grateful, and you want to kick me.

68
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,880
If you were not a woman, I'd─

69
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:51,080
You'd what?

70
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:54,240
What? What?

71
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,760
- Do you want to hurt me?
- Stop! Stop!

72
00:04:56,760 --> 00:05:01,340
If I wanted to hurt you, I would have hurt you when you threw up on me last night.

73
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:04,440
Who? Me?

74
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,918
When did I throw up on you?

75
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:21,300
Come on. Feel free to throw up if you want to.

76
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,540
But don't throw up on my bathroom floor.

77
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:26,740
Otherwise, I'll throw you out of the room.

78
00:05:29,420 --> 00:05:31,320
Throw up.

79
00:05:35,670 --> 00:05:39,677
Dad. Dad, don't abandon me.

80
00:05:39,677 --> 00:05:42,540
I miss you.

81
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:57,180
Are you crying?

82
00:05:58,440 --> 00:06:00,740
I'm lonely.

83
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,958
Please help me.

84
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:13,152
I want...

85
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:20,192
I want...

86
00:06:22,740 --> 00:06:25,320
I... I want to throw up.

87
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:42,010
Crazy woman. So dirty.

88
00:07:30,150 --> 00:07:32,900
Hey, you.

89
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,600
- Are you all right?
- Why is it so dark?

90
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,040
- You─
- Why is it so dark?

91
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,400
It's so dark. I can't see anything.

92
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:42,340
Just open your eyes. Your hair covers your eyes.

93
00:07:42,340 --> 00:07:45,880
- Just push your hair away and open your eyes.
- What?

94
00:07:45,880 --> 00:07:47,680
Open your eyes.

95
00:07:50,660 --> 00:07:52,820
It's actually my hair.

96
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:58,640
I thought it was kelp. Because I'm a mermaid.

97
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:01,060
I am a mermaid.

98
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:04,460
- Splash.
- Hey. Hey.

99
00:08:04,460 --> 00:08:07,200
- Mermaid.
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

100
00:08:07,200 --> 00:08:10,040
The water. You spilled water all over the place.

101
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:12,680
Stop! Stop!

102
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:17,280
Ugh.

103
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:24,000
What are you going to do? What do you want?

104
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:28,460
It's so hot. I'm going to take a shower.

105
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:30,459
Don't take it off...

106
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,060
What's wrong with you?

107
00:08:41,300 --> 00:08:44,740
I feel more comfortable.

108
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:57,680
Aren't you a mermaid?

109
00:08:57,680 --> 00:08:59,480
You can't be out of the water for too long.

110
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:03,180
You need to stay in the water all the time. Otherwise, you will die.

111
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,920
Wait.

112
00:09:09,560 --> 00:09:12,800
Mermaids should stay in the water.

113
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,900
Yes, mermaids should stay in the water.

114
00:09:14,900 --> 00:09:16,500
- Go down.
- Go down.

115
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,460
Mermaids should stay in the water.

116
00:09:19,460 --> 00:09:22,400
I'm in the water.

117
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:40,637
Do you need a towel? Hey.

118
00:09:46,140 --> 00:09:48,060
Are you naked?

119
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:22,740
Is it okay for a man

120
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:25,580
to leave a woman in the water?

121
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:29,260
You're covered in vomit.

122
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:33,020
There are germs everywhere. Just leave her in the water.

123
00:10:33,020 --> 00:10:35,372
It's all right.

124
00:10:35,372 --> 00:10:37,540
You took her home and put her to sleep.

125
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:40,840
It's much better than letting her sleep on the side of the road.

126
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:43,520
But if she stays in the water like this all night,

127
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:47,860
she may get pneumonia, get a virus, or get a fever.

128
00:10:47,860 --> 00:10:50,227
And there are germs in the bathroom.

129
00:10:50,227 --> 00:10:53,680
If she dies,

130
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:56,460
can you afford it?

131
00:10:56,460 --> 00:11:00,860
She asked for it. What does it matter to us?

132
00:11:00,860 --> 00:11:04,920
If she dies of pulmonary edema, won't you feel anything?

133
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:09,960
- No.
- Yes.

134
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:44,700
I covered my eyes. I can't see anything.

135
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,470
Where are you?

136
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:21,680
Whose hand is this?

137
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:23,160
It's mine. Let go.

138
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:25,310
No.

139
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:54,090
- Hey.
- Wait.

140
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,840
Dad, don't leave me.

141
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:00,580
I'm tired.

142
00:13:00,580 --> 00:13:04,713
I'm the one... who's tired.

143
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:07,350
I'm tired.

144
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,520
Dad, I miss you so much.

145
00:13:13,260 --> 00:13:15,500
I miss you.

146
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:19,250
Dad, hug me.

147
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:26,160
I miss you so much.

148
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:31,890
Hug me.

149
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:13,220
Don't leave me.

150
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:14,560
I miss you.

151
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,830
I miss you, Dad.

152
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:22,310
I miss you, Dad.

153
00:14:38,680 --> 00:14:42,646
Why should I believe you aren't lying to me?

154
00:14:42,646 --> 00:14:45,200
If you don't believe it, just take the quilt away.

155
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:49,310
Then, look at yourself. See if you're strapped.

156
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:05,220
How is it? I tied you up tightly.

157
00:15:05,220 --> 00:15:07,720
Do you think I could do it to you?

158
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:09,640
Why didn't you make it clear at the beginning?

159
00:15:09,640 --> 00:15:12,400
Then we wouldn't have these problems.

160
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:14,739
You're still asking "why?"

161
00:15:14,739 --> 00:15:16,740
Now that you know you're wrong,

162
00:15:16,740 --> 00:15:19,740
is it that hard for you to apologize?

163
00:15:19,740 --> 00:15:22,380
Why are you talking about something else?

164
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,810
Sorry.

165
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:35,150
Is that it?

166
00:15:37,180 --> 00:15:38,940
You missed a word.

167
00:15:38,940 --> 00:15:40,960
What word?

168
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:44,570
What should you say when someone helps you?

169
00:15:48,980 --> 00:15:52,120
Thank... you.

170
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,450
What?

171
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,580
Thank you.

172
00:15:57,960 --> 00:16:00,698
Where are my clothes?

173
00:16:00,698 --> 00:16:03,180
I asked the housekeeper to wash them.

174
00:16:03,180 --> 00:16:06,400
There. Your suitcase is there.

175
00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:09,700
Get dressed and meet me in the living room.

176
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,560
I have something important to talk to you.

177
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:19,300
Put my belts away. They're expensive.

178
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:25,030
What's wrong with you?

179
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:29,930
Is that the important thing you wanted to talk to me about?

180
00:16:31,060 --> 00:16:32,490
Yes.

181
00:16:33,420 --> 00:16:35,220
Isn't that important?

182
00:16:35,960 --> 00:16:40,540
GU Center is a famous mall for others. Everybody wants to work there.

183
00:16:40,540 --> 00:16:42,500
But for me,

184
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:45,190
it's just a normal mall.

185
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,460
I don't think so.

186
00:16:50,460 --> 00:16:53,100
You also want to work at GU.

187
00:16:53,100 --> 00:16:57,540
You turned down my offer because you were afraid.

188
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:59,306
What am I afraid of?

189
00:16:59,306 --> 00:17:02,130
There's nothing in GU I can be afraid of.

190
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:06,080
May I ask you something?

191
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:09,460
Do you know what my relationship is...

192
00:17:10,690 --> 00:17:13,070
with Din?

193
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:19,243
I'm sorry. Din and I are not close enough

194
00:17:19,243 --> 00:17:24,000
to know who he was a couple with.

195
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:28,180
We're not a couple.

196
00:17:28,180 --> 00:17:31,840
I am Din's brother.

197
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,709
But I'm not his biological brother.

198
00:17:34,709 --> 00:17:39,010
I know how Din feels about you.

199
00:17:40,220 --> 00:17:43,512
I don't care how he feels about me.

200
00:17:43,512 --> 00:17:46,040
As far as I know, I have nothing to do with him.

201
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:48,820
If there's nothing between you and him, come to work for GU.

202
00:17:48,820 --> 00:17:50,650
No.

203
00:17:54,760 --> 00:17:57,040
I don't want people to point their fingers at me and say,

204
00:17:57,040 --> 00:18:01,020
"She says she doesn't care about it, but she still follows rich people."

205
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:07,420
That's all you want to talk to me about?

206
00:18:07,420 --> 00:18:09,810
Are you talking about the chairwoman?

207
00:18:12,700 --> 00:18:15,186
If you don't want the chairwoman to look down on you,

208
00:18:15,186 --> 00:18:17,150
you shouldn't run away again.

209
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:24,040
You should let her know that you're not pestering Din.

210
00:18:24,573 --> 00:18:26,640
Because you are very capable,

211
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:29,650
you don't need to rely on anyone.

212
00:18:30,580 --> 00:18:33,440
This is your chance to prove yourself

213
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:37,730
and to prove that you didn't plagiarize someone else's design.

214
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,460
If I can prove I didn't plagiarize her design...

215
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:46,460
but she copied mine,

216
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:53,820
will you put aside your pride and fire her?

217
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:59,860
If there's something bad,

218
00:18:59,860 --> 00:19:02,250
I'll clear it in time.

219
00:19:11,580 --> 00:19:13,830
Really, Khun Hom?

220
00:19:15,230 --> 00:19:16,140
You!

221
00:19:16,140 --> 00:19:18,910
- Sorry.
- Be careful. My clothes are─

222
00:19:20,900 --> 00:19:22,940
It's you.

223
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,500
A small part of your clothes is dirty.

224
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:30,510
As a designer, you must have a solution.

225
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:37,220
I don't think you know how to solve it, right? Because you copied someone else's design.

226
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:39,260
What a small world!

227
00:19:39,260 --> 00:19:42,540
There are many coffee shops, but I ran into you at this one.

228
00:19:42,540 --> 00:19:45,100
No, it's not because it's a small world.

229
00:19:45,100 --> 00:19:48,530
It's because you will pay for what you did to me.

230
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:52,780
Well, I'll call you back.

231
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:54,000
You don't have to hang up.

232
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:56,430
I know you're talking to Hom.

233
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:04,100
Where are you going─

234
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:07,360
with your suitcase?

235
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:11,260
Are you going back to wander abroad?

236
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:15,140
You'll be very anxious if I go back abroad.

237
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:18,193
If I'm not here, whose design are you going to plagiarize ?

238
00:20:18,193 --> 00:20:21,380
You're stupid. I don't think you can design it yourself.

239
00:20:21,953 --> 00:20:25,560
If I'm stupid, you're more stupid,

240
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:27,799
because you gave me the chance to plagiarize your design.

241
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:30,910
You finally admitted it, didn't you?

242
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:34,770
What did I just say?

243
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:38,600
Those are empty words. They're useless.

244
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:40,380
It's not like what you did.

245
00:20:40,380 --> 00:20:43,980
You copied my design. And I have proof.

246
00:20:43,980 --> 00:20:47,340
Empty words can't hurt me.

247
00:20:47,340 --> 00:20:50,240
Are you sure you want to provoke me like this?

248
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:54,940
You have no idea how many people I've met worse than you.

249
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:57,180
Are you going to do something to me?

250
00:20:57,180 --> 00:20:58,480
I can't tell you.

251
00:21:01,100 --> 00:21:03,600
Just wait and see.

252
00:21:03,600 --> 00:21:07,100
You'd better tell your relatives what you like to eat.

253
00:21:07,100 --> 00:21:09,350
So that they can bring them to your grave.

254
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,630
I'll leave.

255
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:23,970
Coward.

256
00:21:37,580 --> 00:21:39,240
That will be ฿180 ($5.60).

257
00:21:39,240 --> 00:21:40,710
Okay.

258
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:49,360
Wait a second.

259
00:21:49,360 --> 00:21:50,880
Okay.

260
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:09,693
Hello.

261
00:22:09,693 --> 00:22:11,380
Khun.

262
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,480
How did you call here?

263
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:17,980
I called the mall and asked them to transfer it to you.

264
00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:19,720
Don't ask any questions, okay?

265
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:23,180
I borrowed a waiter's phone to call you.

266
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:29,540
Last night, did you see my wallet, phone, and passport?

267
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:32,380
I saw nothing but you covered in germs.

268
00:22:32,380 --> 00:22:35,600
That's it. I have to go back to work.

269
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:38,940
By the way, remember to consider my advice.

270
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:53,880
Thank you.

271
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:56,040
You're welcome. It's my pleasure.

272
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:11,340
No one found any wallets last night.

273
00:23:11,340 --> 00:23:14,920
Did anyone see that?

274
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,460
Please think it over.

275
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:18,680
Think where you left it.

276
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,880
Could it be...

277
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:36,080
[Postcode: 10260]

278
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:38,280
Khun Kheetika, are you okay?

279
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:39,980
Oh, your stuff is all over the place.

280
00:23:39,980 --> 00:23:41,980
Help.

281
00:23:41,980 --> 00:23:45,520
- My suitcase got hit by a car and flew here.
- Wait.

282
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:49,780
My suitcase is dead!

283
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,740
It's here. Here.

284
00:23:56,400 --> 00:23:57,700
Passport.

285
00:23:59,946 --> 00:24:01,140
Where is it?

286
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:06,200
Where is my wallet, bank card, and credit card?

287
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:16,220
Is God testing me?

288
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:22,420
Come on. Test me! I won't give up.

289
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:24,500
I've been through worse.

290
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:27,243
It's just a little problem.

291
00:24:27,243 --> 00:24:29,500
I'll find a way out.

292
00:24:37,660 --> 00:24:40,940
[GU]

293
00:24:40,940 --> 00:24:43,960
Sorry. My son was swinging the toy bag

294
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:47,220
- and it accidentally slipped out of his hand.
- It's all right.

295
00:24:47,220 --> 00:24:49,340
- Son, apologize to the young lady.
- Sorry.

296
00:24:49,340 --> 00:24:51,760
Hold it tight, son. So you don't swing it and hit someone else's head again.

297
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:52,980
Okay. Let's go.

298
00:24:52,980 --> 00:24:54,100
[GU]

299
00:25:03,500 --> 00:25:05,500
[GU]

300
00:25:21,920 --> 00:25:23,320
Maha.

301
00:25:23,320 --> 00:25:24,480
Yes, Khun Sira.

302
00:25:24,480 --> 00:25:26,560
Make me another cup of coffee.

303
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:28,300
More coffee?

304
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:32,540
You've had three cups of coffee since the meeting.

305
00:25:32,540 --> 00:25:34,680
I think you're tired.

306
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:36,440
I don't think you slept well last night.

307
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:37,940
Let's postpone the meeting to this afternoon.

308
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:40,340
We'll have the meeting this afternoon.

309
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,260
Okay.

310
00:25:43,260 --> 00:25:46,040
We'll come back for the meeting at 1:00 p.m.

311
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:48,140
- Maha.
- Yes.

312
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:50,000
Make a cup of coffee and take it to my office.

313
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:51,600
Okay.

314
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:12,920
You really don't know what Khun Sira did last night?

315
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,840
He looks so tired.

316
00:26:15,960 --> 00:26:19,160
And he was late in the morning. He came just before the meeting.

317
00:26:19,180 --> 00:26:21,260
And he didn't check if the employees were properly dressed.

318
00:26:21,260 --> 00:26:23,680
I called him last night, and he didn't answer.

319
00:26:23,680 --> 00:26:27,120
It couldn't be that he fell asleep and didn't hear the phone ring.

320
00:26:27,720 --> 00:26:32,520
Maybe he was doing something and couldn't answer the phone.

321
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:34,860
What was he doing?

322
00:26:34,860 --> 00:26:37,060
What would Khun Sira do?

323
00:26:37,060 --> 00:26:39,300
He's a bachelor, isn't he?

324
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:44,700
What if he was not alone?

325
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:46,100
He was with a drunk person.

326
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:48,180
A drunk person? Who?

327
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:50,280
Who was drunk?

328
00:26:50,280 --> 00:26:51,440
Could it be...

329
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,180
That's not true!

330
00:26:53,180 --> 00:26:55,440
- No way!
- What?

331
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:59,380
What? What's wrong?

332
00:26:59,380 --> 00:27:00,980
Maha.

333
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:02,660
Come back and clarify it.

334
00:27:02,660 --> 00:27:04,660
I want to know.

335
00:27:04,660 --> 00:27:06,500
Who was drunk?

336
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,320
Khun Sira.

337
00:27:29,620 --> 00:27:31,460
Khun Sira.

338
00:27:36,740 --> 00:27:38,340
Khun Sira!

339
00:27:42,873 --> 00:27:48,387
Well, Khun Sira, which hotel did you drop Khun Kheetika off at last night?

340
00:27:53,460 --> 00:27:57,100
It's great that you mentioned it. So I can make it clear to you.

341
00:27:57,100 --> 00:27:58,460
You left me last night.

342
00:27:58,460 --> 00:28:00,260
Do you know what happened next?

343
00:28:00,260 --> 00:28:02,780
What happened?

344
00:28:02,780 --> 00:28:05,280
You left that woman with me.

345
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:08,140
I didn't sleep all night.

346
00:28:08,140 --> 00:28:10,100
You didn't sleep all night?

347
00:28:10,100 --> 00:28:12,120
Gosh.

348
00:28:14,140 --> 00:28:16,100
My whole body is sore.

349
00:28:16,100 --> 00:28:19,860
I had to do something that I had never done to other women.

350
00:28:19,860 --> 00:28:21,920
Do you know how tired I was?

351
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:29,140
Don't tell me that Khun Kheetika and you slept together or something...

352
00:28:29,780 --> 00:28:31,540
last night.

353
00:28:31,540 --> 00:28:33,340
Maha!

354
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:38,080
I'm telling you. I didn't do the things you said.

355
00:28:38,080 --> 00:28:40,900
You can stop thinking.

356
00:28:40,900 --> 00:28:43,240
What did you do then?

357
00:28:43,240 --> 00:28:45,620
You are tired. Your body is sore.

358
00:28:45,660 --> 00:28:49,000
And you did something you had never done with other women.

359
00:28:55,293 --> 00:28:57,940
I'm tired because I didn't sleep last night.

360
00:28:57,940 --> 00:29:00,260
I had to take care of Kheetika.

361
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:04,780
I did something I had never done with other women because I had...

362
00:29:12,240 --> 00:29:16,140
to wipe her face and take care of her.

363
00:29:19,553 --> 00:29:21,325
Really?

364
00:29:22,860 --> 00:29:24,560
I never lie.

365
00:29:31,820 --> 00:29:34,359
Hold on. I'll answer the phone for you.

366
00:29:35,713 --> 00:29:37,173
Hello.

367
00:29:38,626 --> 00:29:39,680
What?

368
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:42,160
Who wants to see Khun Sira?

369
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:56,780
Khun Kheetika, Khun Sira wants you to wait here for a moment.

370
00:29:56,780 --> 00:29:58,640
He's coming down.

371
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,280
Thank you.

372
00:30:04,180 --> 00:30:09,103
Pimthong, is she the woman who copied our company's design?

373
00:30:09,103 --> 00:30:12,600
Yes, it's her. She's Kheetika.

374
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:14,180
Keep an eye on her.

375
00:30:14,180 --> 00:30:16,820
We can't let her into our mall office.

376
00:30:16,820 --> 00:30:19,200
In case she will plagiarize our designs again.

377
00:30:32,740 --> 00:30:36,220
What do you want to see me about?

378
00:30:36,220 --> 00:30:38,940
You make it sound like we're strangers.

379
00:30:38,940 --> 00:30:41,918
We stayed together all night. Aren't we close enough?

380
00:30:42,860 --> 00:30:44,540
All night.

381
00:31:00,880 --> 00:31:05,066
Please watch your language before you speak.

382
00:31:05,066 --> 00:31:09,840
Your words could get me in trouble.

383
00:31:09,846 --> 00:31:12,813
I'm just kidding.

384
00:31:12,813 --> 00:31:14,973
Do you have to be so serious?

385
00:31:17,940 --> 00:31:21,060
I came to talk about your offer.

386
00:31:21,900 --> 00:31:23,600
Are you serious about that?

387
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:35,820
Assistant of the Design Department? Isn't this position too low, Mr. Vice Chairman?

388
00:31:35,820 --> 00:31:38,040
What position do you want?

389
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:42,714
Head of the Design Department of the New Look website.

390
00:31:42,714 --> 00:31:46,999
The Design Department is a core department of the website.

391
00:31:46,999 --> 00:31:48,977
It's crucial.

392
00:31:48,977 --> 00:31:53,693
I'm not sure about putting you in such an important position.

393
00:31:53,693 --> 00:31:57,632
So, I can't offer you that position.

394
00:31:58,346 --> 00:32:02,080
Then I will refuse your offer.

395
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:04,800
But an assistant in the Design Department

396
00:32:04,800 --> 00:32:07,720
is no different from the head of the Design Department.

397
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:12,040
Because you will have the right to decide on all GU's designs.

398
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:14,285
It's a special position.

399
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:15,780
What do you mean by that?

400
00:32:15,780 --> 00:32:19,480
In addition to being an assistant in the Design Department,

401
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:23,000
you will also be my assistant.

402
00:32:25,780 --> 00:32:28,680
Can you hear them?

403
00:32:28,680 --> 00:32:30,480
No.

404
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:32,160
It's too far.

405
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:34,306
I can't see them either.

406
00:32:34,306 --> 00:32:36,151
What are they talking about?

407
00:33:06,306 --> 00:33:08,280
Rossarin,

408
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:10,253
your eyes...

409
00:33:12,140 --> 00:33:13,940
Do you like them?

410
00:33:14,898 --> 00:33:16,860
You have some sleep crust in your eyes.

411
00:33:18,140 --> 00:33:20,160
Maha

412
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:23,240
What's wrong with you?

413
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:26,910
I told you that you have sleep crust. Just wipe it off.

414
00:33:26,910 --> 00:33:28,680
What's wrong with you?

415
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:30,660
Don't you want to see it, Rossarin?

416
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:32,626
No.

417
00:33:33,260 --> 00:33:34,380
Do you need any help?

418
00:33:34,380 --> 00:33:35,885
No!

419
00:33:36,580 --> 00:33:38,380
What?

420
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,960
You look hesitant.

421
00:33:43,960 --> 00:33:45,700
Are you afraid to work with me?

422
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:47,960
I'm not afraid.

423
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,160
I'm just wondering

424
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:55,100
how much I should ask for to be your assistant.

425
00:33:55,100 --> 00:33:57,700
After all, I'll work with you, a strange guy.

426
00:33:58,500 --> 00:34:01,960
You always talk about money.

427
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,760
Of course.

428
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:06,160
Because it's something important to me.

429
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:08,680
Okay. How much salary do you want?

430
00:34:08,680 --> 00:34:10,900
If it's acceptable, you can sign the contract tomorrow.

431
00:34:10,900 --> 00:34:15,700
But if you plagiarize someone else's design or lie while working here,

432
00:34:15,720 --> 00:34:17,300
I will fire you immediately.

433
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:20,620
And you won't get severance pay.

434
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:24,940
Okay, Mr. Vice Chairman.

435
00:34:24,940 --> 00:34:27,260
You may leave.

436
00:34:34,392 --> 00:34:35,712
Wait.

437
00:34:35,712 --> 00:34:37,985
There's something I need to talk to you about.

438
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,980
That's...

439
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:48,080
The day I got drunk, and you took me home,

440
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:51,820
you collected my stuff. Right?

441
00:34:51,820 --> 00:34:53,000
Yes.

442
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:55,140
Because all your stuff fell out.

443
00:34:55,140 --> 00:34:56,860
Then you must be responsible for me.

444
00:34:56,860 --> 00:34:59,160
You lost my wallet.

445
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:01,220
You lost my credit card and bank card.

446
00:35:01,220 --> 00:35:03,760
I have no money now.

447
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,940
You were drunk, and you lost them yourself.

448
00:35:05,940 --> 00:35:07,980
But you collected my stuff.

449
00:35:07,980 --> 00:35:09,610
Okay.

450
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:13,280
I can give you a chance to make it up.

451
00:35:13,280 --> 00:35:15,880
You lost my wallet.

452
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:20,600
You can advance to me a month's salary.

453
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:23,800
You haven't started working yet.

454
00:35:23,800 --> 00:35:27,020
Are you asking me to give you an advance on your salary?

455
00:35:27,020 --> 00:35:29,700
Because I have no money.

456
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:32,560
And it takes time to apply for new cards.

457
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:34,140
And I'm going to work here.

458
00:35:34,140 --> 00:35:37,400
I need to pay for transportation, food, and rent.

459
00:35:37,400 --> 00:35:43,420
How do I know you won't run away with the money?

460
00:35:43,420 --> 00:35:45,000
I'm not unfaithful.

461
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:48,820
But ever since I met you, you've been lying.

462
00:35:48,820 --> 00:35:51,360
I'm not wrong to think so.

463
00:35:54,898 --> 00:35:57,858
Okay. All right.

464
00:35:57,858 --> 00:36:00,500
If you don't give me an advance,

465
00:36:00,500 --> 00:36:04,220
then I'll stay in your office.

466
00:36:04,220 --> 00:36:08,640
It's not bad. I don't need to pay for transportation or rent.

467
00:36:08,640 --> 00:36:12,780
And I'll eat in your office.

468
00:36:12,780 --> 00:36:15,260
No. Get up.

469
00:36:18,112 --> 00:36:22,680
Then give me an advance.

470
00:36:25,886 --> 00:36:29,147
Okay. If you want an advance,

471
00:36:29,147 --> 00:36:31,800
I'll lend you my money.

472
00:36:32,566 --> 00:36:34,846
As for accommodation,

473
00:36:34,846 --> 00:36:38,400
you must live in the place I arrange for you.

474
00:36:38,400 --> 00:36:40,085
Why?

475
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:46,020
To prove that you won't run away with my money.

476
00:36:47,092 --> 00:36:50,692
Okay. Deal.

477
00:36:51,965 --> 00:36:53,465
Get up.

478
00:37:31,780 --> 00:37:33,673
What's wrong with you?

479
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:41,740
Khun Kheetika, please come in.

480
00:37:42,660 --> 00:37:45,100
My room is a bit small.

481
00:37:45,100 --> 00:37:47,606
Khun Kheetika, you are okay with it. Right?

482
00:37:47,606 --> 00:37:49,640
It's okay.

483
00:37:54,380 --> 00:37:55,560
[Salary]

484
00:37:55,560 --> 00:37:58,820
I'm forgetful. So, I need to write things down.

485
00:37:58,820 --> 00:38:00,700
You may see notes everywhere.
[Don't forget to turn off the lights]
[Don't eat spicy food more than twice a day]

486
00:38:00,700 --> 00:38:02,300
Khun Kheetika, don't worry about it.
[Don't forget to turn off the water.]

487
00:38:02,300 --> 00:38:04,440
[No more than two spoonfuls of sugar a day.]
[Order the meal on the 12th floor.]

488
00:38:06,420 --> 00:38:08,780
Just call me Kanghan.

489
00:38:08,780 --> 00:38:11,020
My nickname is Kanghan.

490
00:38:11,020 --> 00:38:12,780
It's a lovely name.

491
00:38:12,780 --> 00:38:15,420
Khun Kanghan.

492
00:38:15,420 --> 00:38:19,140
Just call me Kanghan.

493
00:38:21,033 --> 00:38:22,240
No.

494
00:38:22,240 --> 00:38:24,300
You're Khun Sira's personal assistant.

495
00:38:24,300 --> 00:38:27,780
He had never hired a personal assistant so easily.

496
00:38:27,780 --> 00:38:30,700
It proves that you're good and capable.

497
00:38:30,700 --> 00:38:35,660
Maybe I should call you Khun Kheetika like I used to.

498
00:38:35,660 --> 00:38:40,560
Okay. Whatever you like.

499
00:38:41,420 --> 00:38:44,140
Thank you for letting me stay here.

500
00:38:44,140 --> 00:38:49,133
I've called my friends in Italy and asked them to help with my credit card.

501
00:38:49,133 --> 00:38:50,593
Because...

502
00:38:50,593 --> 00:38:52,160
Because I just came back.

503
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:55,240
My bank cards were issued by banks in Italy.

504
00:38:55,240 --> 00:39:00,260
I'll try not to trouble you.

505
00:39:01,340 --> 00:39:02,640
It's okay.

506
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:06,100
Khun Kheetika, make yourself at home.

507
00:39:06,100 --> 00:39:09,180
My room is a bit small.

508
00:39:09,180 --> 00:39:11,480
It may be stuffy.

509
00:39:11,500 --> 00:39:16,420
But the advantage of a small room is that it cools quickly and saves energy.

510
00:39:16,420 --> 00:39:17,380
Okay.

511
00:39:17,380 --> 00:39:19,620
You can put your clothes in the closet.

512
00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:23,820
I'll free up the left side of the closet for you later.

513
00:39:23,820 --> 00:39:26,560
But we might have to share a bed.

514
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:29,420
Khun Kheetika, you don't mind. Right?

515
00:39:29,420 --> 00:39:32,700
Khun Rossarin, you sleep on the bed.

516
00:39:32,700 --> 00:39:35,580
I'll sleep on the couch.

517
00:39:35,580 --> 00:39:37,120
No.

518
00:39:37,120 --> 00:39:40,060
Khun Kheetika, we'd better share the bed. That's the perfect solution.

519
00:39:40,080 --> 00:39:42,300
If you want to eat anything or want to use anything,

520
00:39:42,300 --> 00:39:44,500
help yourself.

521
00:39:44,500 --> 00:39:48,260
I'm not worried, and I don't mind.

522
00:39:48,260 --> 00:39:50,300
Okay.

523
00:39:50,300 --> 00:39:53,780
[No sodas. Only drink coffee in the company.]
[No more than two spoonfuls of sugar a day.]

524
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:58,100
Khun Rossarin, are you sure

525
00:39:58,100 --> 00:40:01,700
