526
00:40:03,540 --> 00:40:08,140
Because I'm trying to lose weight, I am dieting.

527
00:40:08,140 --> 00:40:11,640
It has nothing to do with expenses.

528
00:40:11,640 --> 00:40:13,960
Khun Kheetika, don't worry. Just stay here.

529
00:40:13,960 --> 00:40:15,660
You living with me is not a problem for me.

530
00:40:15,660 --> 00:40:19,700
I'll be in trouble if you don't live with me.

531
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:22,420
Do you want Khun Kheetika to live in my house?

532
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:23,500
Yes.

533
00:40:23,500 --> 00:40:26,500
I want you to keep an eye on Kheetika for me.

534
00:40:27,198 --> 00:40:29,858
Why do you want me to keep an eye on her?

535
00:40:31,006 --> 00:40:32,931
Could it be

536
00:40:32,931 --> 00:40:38,040
that the rumor between you and Khun Kheetika is true?

537
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,990
I feel like I'm falling out of love.

538
00:40:39,990 --> 00:40:41,900
You're exaggerating, Khun Rossarin.

539
00:40:41,900 --> 00:40:44,180
Are you kidding me, Rossarin?

540
00:40:44,946 --> 00:40:46,210
No.

541
00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:49,480
Well, Maha told me that. And I believed him.

542
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,500
But I already told Maha

543
00:40:51,500 --> 00:40:55,738
that Khun Sira wouldn't have an affair with someone who copied GU's design.

544
00:40:55,738 --> 00:40:58,525
Rossarin, it's nice of you to think so.

545
00:40:58,525 --> 00:41:01,380
Kheetika is fighting a plagiarism lawsuit.

546
00:41:01,380 --> 00:41:04,192
That's why I want you to keep an eye on her.

547
00:41:04,192 --> 00:41:07,060
I want to know her true self.

548
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:11,220
What do you mean by that?

549
00:41:11,220 --> 00:41:14,253
Nothing. Are you hungry?

550
00:41:14,253 --> 00:41:15,500
No.

551
00:41:15,500 --> 00:41:19,060
I'll make some sandwiches.

552
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:21,060
Khun Kheetika, why don't you take a shower first?

553
00:41:21,060 --> 00:41:23,120
You can eat it after you take a shower.

554
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:26,220
There is shampoo and a soap with a bear pattern in the bathroom.

555
00:41:26,220 --> 00:41:28,220
You can use them.

556
00:41:28,220 --> 00:41:30,360
You can use as much as you want.

557
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:31,420
Okay.

558
00:41:31,420 --> 00:41:32,958
Sandwich.

559
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:06,180
[No perfume after bathing.]
[Go to the perfume department before work.]

560
00:42:06,180 --> 00:42:09,900
[Go to the bathroom before going home.]
[Bring the cleanser to the office to wash face.]

561
00:42:13,420 --> 00:42:17,500
[Save water.]
[Don't go to the bathroom unless you have to.]

562
00:42:37,180 --> 00:42:42,340
So far, I haven't noticed any unusual behavior.

563
00:42:42,340 --> 00:42:43,820
But don't worry, Mr. Vice Chairman.

564
00:42:43,820 --> 00:42:46,680
I promise to do this job well.

565
00:42:46,680 --> 00:42:49,280
I'll keep an eye on Khun Kheetika.

566
00:42:49,280 --> 00:42:53,470
Then I'll report back to you.

567
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:55,419
Okay.

568
00:42:55,419 --> 00:42:57,240
Bye.

569
00:42:58,240 --> 00:42:59,760
Done.

570
00:43:03,460 --> 00:43:07,100
Khun Kheetika, how long have you been standing there?

571
00:43:08,260 --> 00:43:10,820
We need to talk, Khun Rossarin.

572
00:43:10,820 --> 00:43:14,060
Okay.

573
00:43:28,980 --> 00:43:31,639
You're back, Boss.

574
00:43:31,639 --> 00:43:33,505
What are you doing here?

575
00:43:33,505 --> 00:43:35,153
I came to live with you.

576
00:43:35,153 --> 00:43:37,505
How can you live with me? I asked you to live with Rossarin.

577
00:43:37,505 --> 00:43:40,080
It's a waste of time to live with Rossarin.

578
00:43:42,113 --> 00:43:44,516
You want to know my true self, don't you?

579
00:43:44,516 --> 00:43:47,820
- Who told you that?
- It doesn't matter.

580
00:43:47,860 --> 00:43:51,160
I'm right, am I?

581
00:43:53,180 --> 00:43:56,200
I'd like to live with you.

582
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:59,180
So you can see me from the time you get up to the time you go to sleep.

583
00:43:59,180 --> 00:44:02,580
So you can see every detail of my life.

584
00:44:02,580 --> 00:44:06,320
You don't have to let Khun Rossarin keep an eye on me.

585
00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:07,340
What are you going to do?

586
00:44:07,340 --> 00:44:10,000
- Back off.
- No.

587
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:14,220
- I'm going in.
- Let Go!

588
00:44:14,220 --> 00:44:16,940
- No.
- Get out.

589
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:20,780
- Get out of my house.
- No. No.

590
00:44:20,780 --> 00:44:23,580
No.

591
00:44:25,493 --> 00:44:28,500
- You're not going out, are you?
- No.

592
00:44:29,600 --> 00:44:31,400
My clothes.

593
00:44:51,220 --> 00:44:55,360
I've never seen a crazy woman like her.

594
00:45:16,100 --> 00:45:20,560
It would be embarrassing if I went back to Khun Rossarin now.

595
00:45:20,560 --> 00:45:22,660
What should I do?

596
00:46:25,347 --> 00:46:27,167
Excuse me.

597
00:46:27,780 --> 00:46:30,040
Can I help you?

598
00:46:33,720 --> 00:46:36,640
It's you. Ms. Drunkard.

599
00:46:39,300 --> 00:46:41,620
Ms. Drunkard?

600
00:46:42,180 --> 00:46:43,940
I think you got the wrong person.

601
00:46:43,940 --> 00:46:45,940
No, I didn't.

602
00:46:45,940 --> 00:46:48,720
I saw you and P'Sira last night, right?

603
00:46:48,720 --> 00:46:52,800
You were really drunk, and you took off your...

604
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:55,780
What?

605
00:46:55,780 --> 00:46:57,980
You took off your...

606
00:47:00,540 --> 00:47:03,040
You took off your shoes and threw them around.

607
00:47:03,040 --> 00:47:07,220
Speaking of that, why are you sitting here and not going in?

608
00:47:07,220 --> 00:47:09,060
Well...

609
00:47:09,060 --> 00:47:12,740
Is your boyfriend, P'Sira, not back yet?

610
00:47:12,740 --> 00:47:14,920
So you can't get in.

611
00:47:14,920 --> 00:47:17,600
Boyfriend?

612
00:47:19,400 --> 00:47:21,500
Oh, yes.

613
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:22,840
He's back.

614
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:26,180
But he's mad at me. So he

615
00:47:26,180 --> 00:47:28,400
kicked me out.

616
00:47:28,400 --> 00:47:31,780
Did you have a fight?

617
00:47:31,780 --> 00:47:33,380
Yes.

618
00:47:35,180 --> 00:47:37,140
I don't understand why he's angry.

619
00:47:37,140 --> 00:47:39,440
I tried to ask, but he wouldn't say.

620
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:43,660
Is he angry because you were drunk last night?

621
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:48,900
He's angry about that?

622
00:47:48,900 --> 00:47:51,740
I really don't know.

623
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:02,700
Sloppy woman.

624
00:48:17,660 --> 00:48:19,660
What can I do for you?

625
00:48:21,612 --> 00:48:24,140
It's not about me.

626
00:48:24,140 --> 00:48:26,920
It's about your girlfriend.

627
00:48:26,920 --> 00:48:29,020
She wants to explain herself to you.

628
00:48:29,020 --> 00:48:30,900
My girlfriend?

629
00:48:30,900 --> 00:48:32,580
Hi.

630
00:48:32,580 --> 00:48:34,560
What are you doing?

631
00:48:34,560 --> 00:48:39,260
You should talk it over.

632
00:48:39,260 --> 00:48:44,720
Your girlfriend won't be safe if you kick her out.

633
00:48:45,720 --> 00:48:47,940
I think you got this wrong.

634
00:48:47,940 --> 00:48:51,200
- She's not─
- Sorry. I was drunk last night.

635
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:53,960
I didn't mean it. I was really unhappy, so I went to drink.

636
00:48:53,960 --> 00:48:55,440
You don't have to make excuses.

637
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:59,000
I wasn't as drunk as you when I wasn't happy.

638
00:48:59,000 --> 00:49:03,580
Everyone has a different way of dealing with problems.

639
00:49:04,380 --> 00:49:08,420
Okay. It's not good to drink.

640
00:49:08,420 --> 00:49:12,140
But you should talk it over.

641
00:49:12,140 --> 00:49:15,000
I don't think it's a good solution

642
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:17,400
to kick your girlfriend out at night.

643
00:49:19,520 --> 00:49:23,620
I think... I think you got this wrong.

644
00:49:23,620 --> 00:49:27,165
There's nothing between me and her.

645
00:49:30,780 --> 00:49:32,900
If there's nothing between us,

646
00:49:32,900 --> 00:49:35,860
why did you bring me here last night?

647
00:49:35,860 --> 00:49:41,200
Do you think I'm an easy girl that you can bring here whenever you want?

648
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:43,300
What are you talking about?

649
00:49:44,420 --> 00:49:46,380
Don't worry, Miss.

650
00:49:46,380 --> 00:49:50,120
If he doesn't want to talk it over with you or kick you out again,

651
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:54,460
I'll testify for you that he brought you here last night.

652
00:49:55,180 --> 00:49:59,360
Thank you for helping me maintain my dignity as a woman.

653
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:00,960
It's all right.

654
00:50:02,540 --> 00:50:04,620
What are you going to do?

655
00:50:04,620 --> 00:50:08,000
Are we going to talk it over tonight?

656
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:19,680
What kind of woman are you?

657
00:50:19,680 --> 00:50:23,900
You lied to him and said you were my girlfriend.

658
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:26,100
I didn't say that.

659
00:50:26,100 --> 00:50:27,680
You didn't say that?

660
00:50:27,680 --> 00:50:31,480
Then why did he think you were my girlfriend?

661
00:50:32,260 --> 00:50:33,980
Right.

662
00:50:33,980 --> 00:50:36,940
How could he think that?

663
00:50:41,620 --> 00:50:45,160
I carried you in because you were drunk.

664
00:50:45,160 --> 00:50:49,160
You should explain it to him.

665
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:51,220
It's all right. Let him think so.

666
00:50:51,220 --> 00:50:55,020
Anyway, I'm going to live with you for a while.

667
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:58,680
Who agreed to let you live here?

668
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:00,460
I asked you to live with Rossarin.

669
00:51:00,460 --> 00:51:02,820
You want to know me, don't you?

670
00:51:02,820 --> 00:51:05,640
You're afraid I'll run away and not go to work.

671
00:51:05,640 --> 00:51:09,000
So, I'm moving in with you.

672
00:51:09,000 --> 00:51:12,580
So you can see me all the time.

673
00:51:13,200 --> 00:51:16,180
What are you talking about? Are you thinking too much?

674
00:51:16,180 --> 00:51:19,180
You're a woman.

675
00:51:19,180 --> 00:51:23,500
- How can you live with a man?
- Don't worry about it.

676
00:51:23,500 --> 00:51:27,480
When I was abroad, I lived with my male friends. I was safe.

677
00:51:28,060 --> 00:51:32,330
Not to mention that I'm going to live with you.

678
00:51:33,620 --> 00:51:36,200
You have nothing to be afraid of.

679
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:41,180
It's very contemptuous of you...

680
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:45,520
to say that.

681
00:51:53,580 --> 00:51:55,360
See?

682
00:51:55,360 --> 00:51:59,400
It's so easy to deal with a man like you.

683
00:51:59,400 --> 00:52:01,820
Sloppy.

684
00:52:01,820 --> 00:52:04,840
There's no way I'll let you live here.

685
00:52:04,840 --> 00:52:09,060
You. You'd better let me live here.

686
00:52:09,060 --> 00:52:10,860
Otherwise,

687
00:52:12,300 --> 00:52:14,880
I won't work for you.

688
00:52:16,200 --> 00:52:20,260
You're talking like you think you are someone important.

689
00:52:20,260 --> 00:52:22,420
Khun Kheetika.

690
00:52:22,420 --> 00:52:24,580
If I'm not relevant,

691
00:52:24,580 --> 00:52:28,960
why did you, a man of position, offer me the job?

692
00:52:30,320 --> 00:52:31,820
The reason I offered you the job─

693
00:52:31,820 --> 00:52:34,500
Don't say that you wanted me to prove myself.

694
00:52:34,500 --> 00:52:36,780
Because I've thought about it.

695
00:52:36,780 --> 00:52:41,920
Even if I can prove whether I plagiarized or not, it won't bother you. Right?

696
00:52:41,920 --> 00:52:47,460
But you will have trouble...

697
00:52:48,180 --> 00:52:51,740
if you offer me, who has a history of plagiarism, the job.

698
00:52:51,740 --> 00:52:53,080
Well.

699
00:52:53,080 --> 00:52:55,100
You are a businessman.

700
00:52:55,100 --> 00:52:58,180
You weigh the pros and cons before you make decisions.

701
00:52:58,180 --> 00:53:00,860
You won't make money-losing decisions.

702
00:53:00,860 --> 00:53:04,860
Don't tell me that you offered me the job because I'm a good designer.

703
00:53:04,860 --> 00:53:09,060
There's no doubt that GU would find a better designer than me.

704
00:53:12,020 --> 00:53:15,700
I don't know what you want.

705
00:53:15,700 --> 00:53:20,340
But you must want something from me.

706
00:53:21,540 --> 00:53:23,820
So,

707
00:53:25,360 --> 00:53:27,400
you'd better let me live here.

708
00:53:27,400 --> 00:53:32,420
Otherwise, I'm not going to work at GU Center.

